{"id": "duc04-testb-40:8#24", "contents": "President Clinton made a direct appeal to North Korea on Saturday, urging them to abandon their nuclear ambitions and strengthen ties with South Korea and the United States instead. He made this appeal during a meeting with reporters, where he also addressed the situation with Iraq's refusal to comply with a request from weapons inspectors. Clinton emphasized the importance of patience, stating that it was crucial not to overreact on the first day of the crisis. However, he also stressed that Iraq had \"some affirmative obligations\" to help weapons inspectors and that the requested documents were \"quite important.\""}
